CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1967, pg. 17, reads: "AKA Sorrors [sic] - Prior to the ball, this trio of hard-working AKA Sorors got together to look over some of the African pieces which were on display at the group's 'Ajoyo' at the Flying Carpet. From left: Sorors Nan Currington, chairman; Edythe Perkins and Janet Thompson, co-chairman.  The girls planned an excellent evening of social and cultural enjoyment."
TitMainTitle: Woman wearing patterned shirt with solid trim around bottom, cuffs and pocket, standing in domestic interior with armchair and eyeglasses on left
